Message from the Director

The primary goal of the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency’s (OCC’s) Customer Assistance Group (CAG) is to process and resolve consumer complaints, which fall under our jurisdiction, in a fair and expeditious manner. We strive to be recognized as the premier provider of dispute solutions for our financial institutions and customers of those financial institutions. Each complaint we process is approached with the core values of integrity, expertise, collaboration, and independence. The OCC is the prudential regulator for all national banks and federal savings associations and maintains responsibility for all consumer complaints for national banks and federal savings associations with less than $10 billion in assets and for certain consumer complaints, related to the regulations under our purview, for national banks and federal savings associations with assets in excess of $10 billion. On July 21, 2011, the Dodd-Frank Consumer Protection and Wall Street Reform Act, created the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB). The CFPB’s authority includes the handling of consumer complaints related to certain consumer protection laws for banks greater than $10 billion.

Through the CAG, the OCC will continue to address questions and complaints concerning issues under the direct jurisdiction of the OCC. We send any misdirected complaints received to the appropriate federal or state regulator. Consumers can contact the OCC through our website, helpwithmybank.gov or by phone at 1-800-613-6743. The CFPB may be contacted by phone at 1-855-411-2372 or by website at consumerfinance.gov. Consumers may use the FFIEC site to identify a financial institution’s primary regulator, or may use the FDIC institution directory  to identify which institutions have more than $10 billion in assets.

March 2019
